procedures.name: Venipuncture

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), clinical safety laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation), and pregnancy testing.

procedures.name: Urine Collection

code.decode: Urinalysis, by dip stick or tablet reagent

procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screening, pregnancy testing, and 24-hour collection for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Fecal Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content. Each individual sample will be independently collected with record of date, time, and weight.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems. Symptom-driven physical examinations may also be performed.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and clinically significant findings.

procedures.name: Oral Drug Administration
procedures.label: ALXN1840 Administration
procedures.description: Administration of intact ALXN1840 tablets with 240 mL of water after an overnight fast.

procedures.name: Medical History Review
procedures.label: Medical History
procedures.description: Collection of participant medical history, demographics, Wilson disease (WD) history, and prior WD treatment.

procedures.name: Anthropometric Measurement
procedures.label: Height, Weight, BMI
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE/SAE Monitoring
procedures.description: Ongoing monitoring and collection of information on adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs).

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.label: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.description: Screening test for drug use via urine sample.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test

code.decode: Urine pregnancy test, by visual color comparison methods

procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine and/or serum pregnancy tests for females of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Cannula Placement
procedures.label: IV Cannula Placement
procedures.description: Placement of an intravenous cannula to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of samples from all meal and fluid batches for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Neurological Assessment
procedures.label: Neurological Monitoring
procedures.description: Regular monitoring for neurologic adverse events and neurological dysfunction.

procedures.name: Clinical Laboratory Assessments
procedures.label: Safety Labs
procedures.description: Laboratory analysis of blood samples for serum chemistry, hematology, and coagulation parameters.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Device
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device used for assessing blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Intravenous Cannula
medicalDevices.label: IV Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula placed in a vein to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws. Not to be left in place for longer than 72 hours.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometer
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Laboratory equipment used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
